    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="929"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d929">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3394/235: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-11T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 11, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. Send following message to American Embassy at Tokyo by telegraph: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Inquire of appropriate authorities whether following proposed visits of
                            the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Gold Star</hi> are agreeable to Japanese
                            Government: Truk, September 10 to September 12; Palau, September 17 to
                            September 19; Miike, October 12 to October 14; Yokohama, October 18 to
                            October 23; Saipan, October 29 to October 31.<note n="62"
                                xml:id="d929fn62">Truk, Palau, and Saipan were located in the
                                Japanese Mandate.</note> Inform Department by telegraph of reply of
                            Japanese authorities.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
